print(”\n— SECTION 1: THORIUM FUEL CYCLE —”)
print(”””
The Thorium-232 fuel cycle (Th-U233 cycle):

Step 1 — Neutron absorption:
Th-232 + neutron → Th-233

Step 2 — Beta decay chain (rapid):
Th-233 → Pa-233 + beta (half-life: 22 minutes)
Pa-233 → U-233 + beta (half-life: 27 days)

Step 3 — U-233 fission:
U-233 + neutron → fission products + 2.49 neutrons (avg)
Energy per fission: ~200 MeV = 3.2 x 10^-11 Joules

Key advantage: U-233 produces MORE neutrons per absorption
than U-235 or Pu-239 in thermal spectrum reactors.
This enables a BREEDING RATIO > 1.0 in thermal spectrum —
the only fissile material that can do this.
“””)

