# SECTION 3: PASSIVE SAFETY — THE DRAIN TANK

# ============================================================

print(”\n— SECTION 3: PASSIVE SAFETY CHARACTERISTICS —”)
print(”””
The MSR’s most important safety feature requires no pumps,
no operator action, and no electricity. It is pure physics.

THE FREEZE PLUG (Passive Drain System):
─────────────────────────────────────────
A plug of frozen salt seals the drain at the bottom of the reactor.
The plug is kept frozen by a small electric cooling fan.

On loss of power (any cause):
→ Cooling fan stops
→ Plug melts in ~10-15 minutes
→ All fuel salt drains by gravity into subcritical drain tanks
→ Fission stops — permanently, without operator intervention
→ Decay heat dissipates passively into drain tank geometry

This is the opposite of Chernobyl and Fukushima:
Chernobyl: Loss of control WITH power = runaway
Fukushima: Loss of power = loss of cooling = meltdown
MSR:       Loss of power = automatic safe shutdown

NO OPERATOR ACTION REQUIRED. NO BACKUP POWER REQUIRED.
THE REACTOR FAILS INTO A SAFE STATE BY PHYSICS ALONE.
“””)

